The paper proposes a framework for learning compact CNN models with improved classification performance and model generalization. The main focus is on deep learning and convolutional neural networks, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses knowledge distillation, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes an ensemble learning approach, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.DL). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.DL.
